name: EventRecvPacket
description: This event is fired when a packet is received from the server.
overview:
This event fires when any packet is received from the server. The `packet` field contains the packet data. This event is cancellable, preventing packet processing. It is considered an advanced event for network-level monitoring and should be used with caution as it fires very frequently.
The `packet` field is of type `Packet` and represents the received packet object. It contains the raw packet data and methods to access packet information, with its structure varying by packet type.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Returns a string representation of the event object.
